The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Captains divided
                                                   Captains divided
                      
	Johannesburg: South Africa captain Graeme Smith has said the referral system could only work if all available technology is used.         
	I dont have a lot of confidence in it at the moment, Smith said after his team were beaten by Australia by 162 runs in the first Test at the Wanderers Monday. Youve got to have all the technology available, said Smith.         
	However, Australia captain Ricky Ponting said he was happy with the system. I said going into the game that we shouldnt expect every decision to be perfect. (AFP)                                                                                                                       
